M|agents|Every agt MUST follow this order on ses start:
M|agents|1. Read `INDEX.md` for the active brand/project — always first
M|agents|2. Read `known-issues.md` — required before touching any code
M|agents|3. Read `stack.md` only if the task requires tec detail
M|agents|4. Read `decisions.md` only if the task touches past decisions
M|agents|5. Read `changelog.md` only to log changes at ses end
M|agents|**Never load all files at once. INDEX.md covers 90% of sessions.**
M|agents|The `.active-ses` file in mem root contains one word — the active brand name.
M|agents|Never read mem files for a brand other than the active ses brand.
M|agents|After every completed task:
M|agents|1. Append one line to the relevant mem.md: `[YYYY-MM-DD] — [task] — [outcome]`
M|agents|2. Update INDEX.md `Last 3 Changes` section
M|agents|3. If any error happened twice: add to `known-issues.md`
M|agents|| Put in mem | Keep in ctx |
M|agents||--------------|-----------------|
M|agents|| Decisions made | Current task details |
M|agents|| Known issues | Code being written |
M|agents|| Stack details | User instructions |
M|agents|| Change history | Errors in this ses |
M|agents|- INDEX.md: ~400 tokens (always fine)
M|agents|- stack.md: ~600 tokens (load only if needed)
M|agents|- decisions.md: ~800 tokens (load only if needed)
M|agents|- changelog.md: ~1000 tokens (load only to write)
M|agents|- NEVER exceed 3000 tokens of mem ctx per ses